doc/blacksmith-giant-hammer.html.title: Blacksmith Giant Hammer
doc/blacksmith-giant-hammer.html.body:
Blacksmith Giant Hammer
95. How to get Blacksmith Giant Hammer, Dark Souls: Remastered
The Blacksmith Giant Hammer is the best melee lightning weapon for an SL1
character. If you want, you can kill the Giant Blacksmith to collect his
Blacksmith Giant Hammer but only do so after you are certain you would not need
his services for the rest of your playthrough. In particular, he sells Twinkling
Titanites. Ensure you have at least Twinkling Titanite x 10 prior to killing the
Giant Blacksmith because you need those upgrade materials to fully upgrade the
Blacksmith Giant Hammer to +5. While the Blacksmith Giant Hammer+5 deals more
lightning damage than the Lightning Reinforced Club+5, note that the latter
weapon deals more physical damage.
You do not need to kill the Giant Blacksmith now for the purpose of stealing his
Blacksmith Giant Hammer. Wait until near the end of the game before you fight
Gwyn. In the meantime, the Lightning Reinforced Club+5 is sufficient for dealing
with bosses who are weak against lightning.

doc/gwyn.html.title: Gwyn, Lord of Cinder
doc/gwyn.html.body:
Gwyn, Lord of Cinder
You are now near the end of your SL1 journey. One more boss remains to be
defeated. Before fighting the final boss, do whatever you need to do and
complete whatever quest line you need to complete. In particular, stock up on
consumables and upgrade materials. Upgrades and/or ascend weapons you want to
experiment in NG+1.
Kiln of the First Flame
If you have not already done so, sit at the bonfire before the kiln and offer
the Lord Souls to open the gate to the kiln. Farm the Black Knights within to
stock up on Titanite Chunks and Blue/Red/White Titanite Chunks.
Gwyn, Lord of Cinder
96. SL1 Gwyn, Lord of Cinder, Dark Souls: Remastered
Equip the Chaos Reinforced Club+4 (a +5 is better if you have it) and have at
least 10 soft Humanities. Equip the Grass Crest Shield and the Mask of the
Child. Trigger the effect of the Red Tearstone Ring. The most effective strategy
against Gwyn is to parry his horizontal swing attacks. Enter the fog wall and
move in some distance toward Gwyn. Wait for him to perform a flying dash at you
and slash his sword. Parry the attack and riposte. Strafe behind Gwyn and R1.
Roll through his attacks as necessary. You can manipulate Gwyn into performing
the horizontal swing attack so you can parry and riposte. After strafing behind
Gwyn, drink from your Estus Flask and Gwyn would perform a horizontal swing of
his sword. Parry the attack and riposte. Rinse and repeat.

doc/conclusion.html.title: Conclusion
doc/conclusion.html.body:
Conclusion
Congratulations on finishing your SL1 playthrough without using pyromancy to
cheese bosses. Other challenges await, including:

An SL1 playthrough where you use pyromancy to fight all bosses. Most or all
bosses can be one-shot with a pyromancy and Red Tearstone Ring setup.
Complete an SL1 NG+7 playthrough.
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLYk2EK7EngpkYXIlvo9fglTAqD63WLqoe

An SL1 playthrough without taking any hits from enemies.
Dark Souls Remastered SL1 All Bosses 0 Hit Run (No Pyromancy)

Invent your own SL1 challenge.

doc/introduction.html.title: Introduction
doc/introduction.html.body:
Introduction
This is a guide to your first SL1 run of Dark Souls: Remastered. We will discuss
tips and strategies to help you overcome your first SL1 challenge. You might
find the following tips useful.

At the character creation screen, choose "Pyromancer" as the starting class
because that is the only class that starts you off at SL1. You play as a
pyromancer, but the challenge is to never level up because an SL1 run means
you must always stay at soul level 1. However, you are allowed to upgrade any
weapon of your choosing. Refer to the following image for reference:
 

Your starting gift can be any item you want. The "Master Key" is recommended.
For extra challenge, choose any starting gift but the "Master Key". The Black
Firebomb allows you to make quick work of the Asylum Demon.

Pyromancy is over-powered even for an SL1 character. You can easily defeat
most if not all bosses by using pyromancy alone. However, this guide is
primarily focused on melee strategies for fighting bosses as an SL1
character. No pyromancy allowed against bosses, not even Power Within.
The Reinforced Club is one of the best weapons for an SL1 character. The
weapon has built-in bleed effect, useful against many bosses. Purchase a
number of copies of the Reinforced Club from the Undead Male Merchant at
Undead Burg and upgrade each copy along a different elemental path. For
example, have one copy of the Reinforced Club upgraded along the magic path,
one copy upgraded along the fire path, etc. The best attack of the Reinforced
Club is the two-handed R2 because it hits hard and allows you to quickly
close the distance.
Armour is not important for an SL1 character because your character would
most likely die to a boss in one or two hits. Prioritize fashion and ensure
your character is fast rolling, i.e. be under 25% equip load. If your
character would die within at most two hits, it might as well die in style.
However, you might want to equip armour pieces that provide high defense to
help you tank one or more hits, thus affording you opportunities to learn a
boss' attack patterns.
Use a bow and arrows to help you pull one enemy at a time for one-to-one
combat. Crossbows are not as effective for pulling because you must free aim
a crossbow.
Rings and other equipment that have special effects are particularly useful.
For example, the Ring of Favor and Protection (aka the FAP ring) boosts your
maximum HP, Stamina, and equipment load. To raise your maximum equipment load
even further, stack the effect of the FAP ring with Havel's Ring and Mask of
the Father. As another example, the Grass Crest Shield boosts your Stamina
regeneration. The effect stacks with the effects of Mask of the Child,
Cloranthy Ring, and Green Blossoms (and Power Within).
For best damage output, equip the Red Tearstone Ring and decrease your HP low
enough to trigger the ring's effect. The Symbol of Avarice is the best item
for lowering your HP. Farm the head piece as soon as possible. The earliest
in the game where you can farm the Symbol of Avarice is at Sen's Fortress.
Familiarity is key to a successful SL1 playthrough. You should know the game
well enough to recognize what is ahead of you, including enemies and
terrains. You do not need to know the attack patterns of every enemy in the
game. However, it helps to learn the attack patterns of some powerful enemies
such as Serpent Soldier, Silver Knight, Black Knight, Berenike Knight, etc.
The Silver Knights at Anor Londo can be one of the biggest hurdles in an SL1
playthrough, but it does not have to be that way. Equip a medium shield, such
as the Grass Crest Shield, and learn to parry each Silver Knight you
encounter. Similarly, learn to parry the Serpent Soldiers at Sen's Fortress
and The Duke's Archives.
Learn from your mistakes and the experiences of other players. An SL1
playthrough can be frustrating, but also rewarding. Your squishy character
would die over and over again. Do not let that fact deter you. With a little
bit of determination and hard work, you can overcome the challenge. At times,
you might be stuck on a particular area or boss and unable to figure out a
strategy. Learn from no-hit runners and incorporate their strategies into
your gameplay. You might find the following videos useful:
 Dark Souls - SL1 No Hit Run (no leveling up)
 Dark Souls Remastered - SL1 No-Hit Any%
 Dark Souls Remastered SL1 All Bosses 0 Hit Run (No Pyromancy)

doc/northern-undead-asylum.html.title: Northern Undead Asylum
doc/northern-undead-asylum.html.body:
Northern Undead Asylum
In which you grab your pyromancer starting gears and break out of a sanatorium.
1. An SL1 runner is born, Dark Souls: Remastered
The beginning is no different from your first regular playthrough. Break out of
your jail cell and make your way to the first bonfire. Light the bonfire and
rest. Open the door to the arena of the Asylum Demon, but do not engage it yet
because you need to first collect your pyromancer starting equipment. Upon
entering the arena, head for the entrance that is diagonally to your left.
Another bonfire is located nearby. Light that bonfire and rest as necessary.
Exit via the other opening to collect the Cracked Round Shield and the Hand Axe.
The latter will be your weapon for the upcoming boss fight. Enter the fog wall,
descend a flight of stairs, and open a shortcut to the first bonfire. Use the
giant metal boulder to break a wall and speak to Oscar to receive your Estus
Flask and the Undead Asylum F2 East Key. Ascend a flight of stairs, open the
locked gate, and collect the Pyromancy Flame. Although this guide will not
discuss pyromancy strategies against bosses, you are still encouraged to use
pyromancy against regular enemies. The Pyromancy Flame allows you to cast
Fireball; use it whenever you need a ranged strategy against regular enemies.
Asylum Demon
2. SL1 Asylum Demon, Dark Souls: Remastered
This tutorial boss is the same as any playthrough. Two-hand the Hand Axe and
initiate the fight by performing a plunging attack to drain the HP bar of the
boss by approximately one-third. The remainder of the fight is about positioning
your character behind the boss, get in one or two hits, and move outside the
range of the boss' attacks.
3. Northern Undead Asylum, Soul of a Lost Undead, Dark Souls: Remastered
Defeat the Asylum Demon, open the door, and exit the arena to collect a Soul of
a Lost Undead. Let the giant crow carry you to Firelink Shrine.

doc/reinforced-club+5.html.title: Reinforced Club+5
doc/reinforced-club+5.html.body:
Reinforced Club+5
The Reinforced Club will be your main weapon for the remainder of your SL1
playthrough. This weapon is recommended for two reasons. First, it has built-in
300 points of bleed effect, useful against these bosses:

Asylum Demon, 75 bleed resistance. Can proc bleed within a few hits.
Bell Gargoyles, 230 bleed resistance. You might kill the boss before bleed
is proc.
Black Dragon Kalameet, 333 bleed resistance. You might not proc bleed for
the entirety of the fight.
Capra Demon, 220 bleed resistance.
Centipede Demon, 195 bleed resistance.
Chaos Witch Quelaag, 110 bleed resistance. Can proc bleed within a few hits.
Crossbreed Priscilla, 125 bleed resistance. Can proc bleed within a few
hits, but not likely while the boss is invisible.
Dark Sun Gwyndolin, 160 bleed resistance. You might not proc bleed because
the interval between opportunities to deal damage can be long.
Demon Firesage, 75 bleed resistance. Can proc bleed within a few hits.
Dragon Slayer Ornstein, 240 bleed resistance in both regular and giant
forms. Might not proc bleed at all.
Executioner Smough, 120 bleed resistance in both regular and giant forms.
Gaping Dragon, 118 bleed resistance.
Pinwheel, 200 bleed resistance.
Sanctuary Guardian, 100 bleed resistance.
Sif, the Great Grey Wolf, 200 bleed resistance.
Stray Demon, 75 bleed resistance. Generally cannot proc bleed during NG+0 of
your SL1 playthrough because you do not yet have access to a weapon that can
build up bleed.
Taurus Demon, 150 bleed resistance. Can proc bleed within a few hits, but is
usually dead before being bled.

Second, the Reinforced Club has a jumping R2 attack, which can quickly close the
distance between your character and an enemy. Feel free to also use other
weapons that suit your play style.
Your current objective is to purchase Reinforced Club x 2 from the Undead Male
Merchant at Undead Burg, then visit Andre at Undead Parish to upgrade a
Reinforced Club to +5.
Firelink Shrine
4. Firelink Shrine, souls and miscellaneous items, Dark Souls: Remastered
Various treasures are scattered around Firelink Shrine. Run around to collect as
many of these treasures as you can. Stay away from the graveyard area because
your current damage output is too paltry for fighting the skeletons. Here is a
list of useful items early in the game.

Humanity x 3
Soul of a Lost Undead x 6
Ring of Sacrifice
Firebomb x 6
Morning Star. A weapon that can bleed any enemy vulnerable to bleed. You
have enough stats to wield this weapon even one-handed.
Homeward Bone x 6
Lloyd's Talisman x 4. Will be used later on to farm for the Symbol of
Avarice. You can also purchase Lloyd's Talismans from the Undead Male
Merchant at Undead Burg.

Undead Burg
5. Undead Burg: Titanite Chunk, Twinkling Titanite x 2, Blue Tearstone Ring, Dark Souls: Remastered
This area has various weapons and upgrade materials you need. You will also
encounter the Undead Male Merchant who sells the Reinforced Club that can be
used as your primary weapon during the course of your SL1 playthrough. Here is a
list of useful items.

Soul of a Lost Undead x 3
Large Soul of a Lost Undead
Rubbish. Will be used later on to trade with Snuggly for a Titanite Chunk.
Humanity
Residence Key. Sold by the Undead Male Merchant. Will be used to rescue
Griggs. Not mandatory for an SL1 playthrough.
Reinforced Club x 2. Purchase these from the Undead Male Merchant. These
will be your main weapons for the rest of the playthrough. As you progress
in the game, purchase a few more copies of the Reinforced Club and upgrade
each along a different upgrade path.
Heater Shield. Purchase this from the Undead Male Merchant. The shield has
100% physical block, useful for situations where you need to block an attack
while sprinting around Lordran.
Standard Bolts and/or Wood Bolts. You do not have enough stats to properly
wield any bow. However, you can wield the Light Crossbow even one-handed.
Purchase as many bolts as you can for now. The Light Crossbow is available
to be collected in the area. You will need to perform a feat of parkour to
collect the weapon.
Repairbox. Sold by the Undead Male Merchant. Use the item to repair your
weapons and armour pieces while sitting at a bonfire.
Black Firebomb x 5
Gold Pine Resin x 3. Will be useful against various upcoming bosses.
Titanite Chunk. Guaranteed drop from the Black Knight in the area. Block
with the Heater Shield while strafing behind the knight for a backstab.
Alternatively, use the shield to parry the knight and follow up with a
riposte.
Blue Tearstone Ring. Guarded by the Black Knight. Equip the ring to allow
you to survive at least one attack from most strong enemies.
Twinkling Titanite x 2. Guaranteed drop from the Crystal Lizard that hides
in a barrel near the fog wall of the area boss. If you are lucky, the lizard
might also drop a Titanite Chunk.

Taurus Demon (optional)
6. SL1 Taurus Demon, Dark Souls: Remastered
Prior to initiating the fight, climb the ladder and defeat the Hollow Soldier x
2 at the top of a tower, otherwise they would snipe you with bolts while you are
fighting the boss. Trigger the boss to appear, run back to the ladder, ascend
the ladder to reach the top of the tower, and wait for the boss to be at the
foot of the tower. Buff the Reinforced Club with Gold Pine Resin, two-hand the
weapon, and perform a plunging attack. Another R1 x 3 should stagger the demon
and a fourth R1 would finish it off.
Darkroot Garden
Defeat the Taurus Demon, find and exhaust the dialogue of Solaire \[T]/ and
answer "Yes" to his question, trigger the appearance of the Hellkite Drake, and
unlock a shortcut to the bonfire at Undead Burg. From the bonfire, enter the
tower where you fought the Taurus demon. Use the Master Key to open a door and
you would find a flight of descending spiral staircase, at the bottom of which
Havel awaits you. Do not fight Havel yet. Bait Havel to run up the staircase,
then sprint to the door to open it and exit the tower to find yourself at the
base of Darkroot Garden.
Here are some useful items in the area.

Large Soul of a Nameless Soldier
Blue Titanite Chunk. Guaranteed drop by the glaive-wielding Black Knight.
Strafe behind the knight to backstab and/or bait the enemy into falling off
the edge to their doom.
Grass Crest Shield. Useful for Stamina regeneration at a rate of 10
points/second. The effect stacks with Green Blossom (40 points/second for 60
seconds), Mask of the Child (10 points/ second), Cloranthy Ring (20
points/second), and Power Within (30 points/second for 100 seconds). Note
that Green Blossom and Power Within do not stack because each is counted as
a body buff. Using one would cancel the other. The maximum amount of Stamina
regeneration you can have is Grass Crest Shield, Green Blossom, Mask of the
Child, and Cloranthy Ring for a total of 80 points/second. Grab the Grass
Crest Shield and equip it in the left hand.
Longbow. You do not have the stats to proper wield the Longbow. However, the
bow can be used to lure a distant enemy to you so you can engage in
one-on-one combat. Bows in the game allow you to aim, whereas crossbows do
not have the aiming feature. You can still aim your Light Crossbow as
follows. Equip a bow in the left hand and the Light Crossbow in the right
hand. Two-hand the bow and use it to aim at a target. Then switch to the
Light Crossbow and shoot a bolt. The shot would hit the target and/or the
general area around the target. This strategy requires some practice to get
right.
Twinkling Titanite x 2. Guaranteed drop from a Crystal Lizard. You might get
lucky and it would also drop a Titanite Chunk.

Undead Parish
8. Undead Parish: Titanite Shard, Dark Souls: Remastered
Purchase Titanite Shard x 9 from Andre and upgrade a Reinforced Club to +5.
Titanite Shards can also be farmed from enemies in this area.

doc/fap-ring.html.title: Ring of Favor and Protection
doc/fap-ring.html.body:
Ring of Favor and Protection
The Ring of Favor and Protection, aka the FAP ring, boosts your maximum HP,
Stamina, and equipment load. It is one of the useful rings for an SL1 character
because you need as much Stamina as you can get being so low level. Once
equipped, the ring would break if you remove it. The FAP ring can be collected
by following Lautrec's quest line.
Firelink Shrine
10. Location of Undead Asylum F2 West Key, Dark Souls: Remastered
Later on, you want to revisit the Northern Undead Asylum to collect various
items that will be useful later in the game. Collecting one of these items
requires a key found on the roof of a building at Firelink Shrine. Start from
the Undead Parish bonfire and sprint to the elevator that takes you to Firelink
Shrine. Before riding the elevator, ensure you have collected the Fire Keeper
Soul guarded by a Berenike Knight. Ride the elevator down and drop off onto a
platform just before the elevator halts. Roll off an edge and onto a buttress,
and ascend a flight of stairs enough that you are above the roof of a building
where you can see a shiny. This is the Undead Asylum F2 West Key.
New Londo Ruins
11. New Londo Ruins: Fire Keeper Soul, Dark Souls: Remastered
A Fire Keeper Soul is found in New Londo Ruins. The item is guarded by various
ghosts hiding in ambush. An easy way to collect the item is to make a suicide
run, grab the item, and jump or roll off the edge to your doom. Ensure you first
spend all souls in your soul counter. On your way to New Londo Ruins, remember
to collect a Soul of a Nameless Soldier.
Undead Parish
Collect the Basement Key, which will be used to access the lower portion of
Undead Burg. The key is found on a corpse, near a lever and a Fang Boar. Rescue
Lautrec from his jail cell and exhaust his dialogue. The cell can be opened by
the Master Key. You want Lautrec to relocate to Firelink Shrine so you can loot
a ring off him.
Bell Gargoyles
12. SL1 Bell Gargoyles, Dark Souls: Remastered
Buff your Reinforced Club+5 with Gold Pine Resin. Two-hand the weapon and
perform R2 x 3 to defeat the first gargoyle. Strafe to your right to avoid the
gargoyle's two-handed overhead attack or the one-handed thrust. Use the same
strafing strategy against the second gargoyle when it breathes fire at you. R2 x
2 should finish off the second gargoyle.
Defeat the Bell Gargoyles and ring the bell atop the tower.
Firelink Shrine
13. How to get Ring of Favor and Protection (FAP Ring), Dark Souls: Remastered
Lautrec should now be sitting in front of the cell of Anastacia. Exhaust
Lautrec's dialogue and he would gift you a Sunlight Medal. The item will be used
later on to trade with Snuggly for a White Titanite Chunk. Collect the Sunlight
Medal, then kick Lautrec off the edge to kill him. Attacking Lautrec in any way
other than kicking him would trigger him to retaliate. The safest strategy is to
kick him off an edge to his doom. Quit and reload your game, and a shiny would
appear where Lautrec previously sat. This shiny is the FAP ring (i.e. Ring of
Favor and Protection). The ring boosts your maximum HP, Stamina, and equipment
load by 20%. The caveat is that you must keep the ring equipped for the rest of
your playthrough; unequipping the ring would break it.

doc/reinforced-club+10.html.title: Reinforced Club+10
doc/reinforced-club+10.html.body:
Reinforced Club+10
At this point in your playthrough, you cannot purchase Large Titanite Shards.
These upgrade materials must be farmed from the Giant Leeches in Lower
Blighttown. The enemies also drop Green Titanite Shards, useful for upgrading a
Reinforced Club along the Divine, Fire, or Magic path.
Lower Blighttown
22. Lower Blighttown: Fire Keeper Soul, Dark Souls: Remastered
Start from Firelink Shrine. Use the Master Key to allow you access to the lower
portion of Blighttown. Have the Spider Shield ready to block the Infested
Barbarians and Blowdart Snipers. Also bring along some Purple Moss Clumps and
Blooming Purple Moss Clumps, all of which can be purchased from the Undead
Female Merchant. Use the Heavy/Light Crossbow and bolts to snipe the Giant
Mosquitos. Make a suicide run to grab the Fire Keeper Soul or play it safe and
snipe the Flaming Attack Dogs first. Useful items to pick up along the way:

Large Soul of a Nameless Soldier
Soul of a Proud Knight

23. Lower Blighttown: Green Titanite Shard & Large Titanite Shard x 2, Dark Souls: Remastered
24. SL1 Lower Blighttown: farm Green Titanite Shards & Large Titanite Shards, Dark Souls: Remastered
Lower Blighttown has a bunch of Giant Leeches that can be used to farm for Large
Titanite Shards and Green Titanite Shards. You will need Green Titanite Shards
to upgrade a weapon along the Divine, Fire, or Magic path. Large Titanite Shards
are used in the standard upgrade path to upgrade weapons to +10. Have 10 soft
Humanities in your Humanities counter to increase your Item Discovery to 210.
Equip the Rusted Iron Ring to allow you to dash unhindered by the swamp. Here
are some useful items to collect in the area:

Large Soul of a Proud Knight x 3
Green Titanite Shard
Large Titanite Shard x 2
Poison Mist. Can be used to kill the red-eyed Chaos Bug that drops the
Sunlight Maggot.
Tattered Cloth set. Collected along with Poison Mist. Boosts your fire
defense.

Collect and/or farm at least Large Titanite Shard x 8 and use them to upgrade
the Reinforced Club+6 to +10. You should have bought the Weapon Smithbox from
Andre.
Chaos Witch Quelaag
25. SL1 Chaos Witch Quelaag, Dark Souls: Remastered
Two-hand the Reinforced Club+10 and buff it with Gold Pine Resin. Equip these to
help you survive an area-of-effect (AOE) blast: Tattered Cloth Manchette, Black
Leather Boots, Blue Tearstone Ring. Stay to the boss' side, not in front and not
behind. Use the R2 to close the distance and get in one hit. When the boss bends
down the upper half of her body and bobs her head, it means she is about to
perform her AOE blast. Run and/or roll away as far as you can to get out of the
range of the AOE. The delayed lava vomit gives you plenty of time to get in 2
hits.
Defeat Quelaag and ring the second Bell of Awakening. Descend the spiral
staircase and light the bonfire next to Quelaag's Sister. This bonfire will be
used later on to access Demon Ruins.

doc/large-magic-ember.html.title: Large Magic Ember
doc/large-magic-ember.html.body:
Large Magic Ember
You are now ready to fight the last boss of the game, i.e. Gwyn. Before doing
so, you might want to grab the Large Magic Ember and/or enter the DLC.
The Large Magic Ember allows Rickert to ascend a magic weapon from +5 to +6. You
need Blue Titanite Chunks and a Blue Titanite Slab to fully upgrade a magic
weapon. Some bosses have magic as their weakest elemental defense:

Ceaseless Discharge. You can easily defeat this boss with any weapon or even
your character's fist. You do not really need the Large Magic Ember to fight
this boss. Should be already defeated.
Centipede Demon. Should be already defeated.
Ornstein, both regular and giant versions. Should be already defeated.

A magic weapon is effective against bosses you have already defeated. Grab the
Large Magic Ember in this playthrough to ascend various weapons to at least +6,
as preparation for later NG cycles.
Not planning on doing SL1 in NG+1? Then head straight to the DLC. Don't want to
do the DLC as well? Go to the Kiln of the First Flame to fight Gwyn and finish
your SL1 playthrough.
Kiln of the First Flame
83. SL1 Kiln of the First Flame: farm (Red/White/Blue) Titanite Chunks, Dark Souls: Remastered
You should now be able to open the gates to the Kiln of the First Flame. Farm
the Black Knights within the kiln for these upgrade materials: Titanite Chunks
and Red/White/Blue Titanite Chunks. Upgrade your weapons in this playthrough as
high as possible so that in the next NG cycle you can max them out. The Black
Knights are easy to parry and backstab, but it is generally safer to backstab.
The Duke's Archives
84. Location of Large Magic Ember, Dark Souls: Remastered
Return to the arena where you first encountered Seath at the top of his tower.
If you have been following Logan's quest line, he should appear in the arena.
Logan is now hostile towards you and will fight you as soon as you enter the
arena. Defeat Logan and grab the Large Magic Ember from the nearby wooden chest.
A Soul of a Great Hero can be found nearby.
Sanctuary Garden
It is time to enter the DLC. Return to the location at Darkroot Basin where you
fought the golden Crystal Golem to rescue Dusk. You should see a dark vortex.
Interact with the vortex to be transported to Sanctuary Garden. Light the
bonfire and prepare to fight the area boss.
Sanctuary Guardian (optional)
85. SL1 Sanctuary Guardian, Dark Souls: Remastered
This boss is weak against fire. Two-hand the Fire Reinforced Club+10. Equip all
items to boost your Stamina regeneration: Grass Crest Shield, Mask of the Child,
and Cloranthy Ring. Bait a swooping attack, roll out of the way, run to the
tail, and R2 to attack the tail. You want to cut off the tail as it can poison
you. Stay in front of the boss and move backward or roll to avoid its attacks.
Then R2 to quickly close the distance and get in a hit. Beware of the lightning
attack because it can linger quite a bit after hitting the water.
86. Royal Wood: Blue Titanite Slab & Elizabeth Mushroom, Dark Souls: Remastered
Defeat the Sanctuary Guardian and enter the Oolacile Sanctuary to light the
nearby bonfire. Exhaust the dialogue of Elizabeth the giant mushroom and accept
her quest to rescue Dusk. Push ahead to the Royal Wood to grab a Blue Titanite
Slab. You will find mostly Wooden Scarecrows, which are easy to fight
one-on-one. Use the Longbow and arrows to lure each Wooden Scarecrow to you one
at a time. The enemies you should be wary of are the Guardians. These enemies
hit hard. Bait an attack and R2. The Blue Titanite Slab is found inside a chest
hidden within a bush and located on a small pool of water. Other useful items to
collect include:

Elizabeth's Mushroom
Soul of a Brave Warrior x 2
Large Soul of a Brave Warrior
Soul of a Proud Knight
Large Soul of a Proud Knight

Knight Artorias (optional)
87. SL1 Knight Artorias, Dark Souls: Remastered
Always lock on to the boss. This boss has high resistance against all elemental
effects and is immune to all auxiliary effects. One way to deal high damage
output is to two-hand the Lightning Reinforced Club+5 and trigger the effect of
the Red Tearstone Ring. Equip the Mask of the Child and the Grass Crest Shield
to boost your Stamina regeneration. Artorias is aggressive. A window to safely
deal an R2 is after his jumping attack. He would crouch for a fraction of a
second, jump in the air, and impale his sword at you. As he crouches, dash
towards him and he would jump over your head and his attack would miss you. Then
R2 and back away. You should generally roll backward and away from his swipe
attacks. Artorias tends to perform a forward roll attack where he slams his
sword after performing a forward flip at you. Roll to your right and be prepared
for another flip, possibly two more, then R2. Another safe window to punish is
after his dashing thrust attack. He would dash towards you and thrust his sword.
Roll to your right, then R2. After depleting about a quarter of his HP bar,
Artorias would roll back two times to begin buffing himself. If you are close
enough, sprint towards him. R2 and an R1 should knock him out of his buffing
animation.
Defeat Artorias and light the Oolacile Township bonfire.

doc/sunlight-maggot.html.title: Sunlight Maggot
doc/sunlight-maggot.html.body:
Sunlight Maggot
The Sunlight Maggot is a head piece that provides a constant source of light.
The item is dropped by the red-eyed Chaos Bug at Demon Ruins. Having a source of
light is especially useful in the Tomb of the Giants, where it is almost pitch
black everywhere. The sorcery Cast Light can also be used to provide
illumination for 5 minutes and requires 14 Intelligence, stat that an SL1
character does not have. Like the Sunlight Maggot, the Skull Lantern provides a
constant source of light. However, you must equip the Skull Lantern in one hand
whereas the Sunlight Maggot frees both hands for the Grass Crest Shield and a
weapon. Obtaining the Sunlight Maggot early would also help to save Solaire from
going insane and trying to attack you. Overall, kill the red-eyed Chaos Bug, not
your sunbro \[T]/.
The Sunlight Maggot can also be used to obtain the Silver Pendant, an item found
in the DLC. While equipped, the Silver Pendant can be used to deflect magic
projectiles. The latter feature is especially useful against bosses who fire
magic at you. In particular, you might find the pendant useful during the fight
against Manus.
Prowling Demon (aka Titanite Demon, optional)
45. SL1 Prowling Demon at Undead Parish, Dark Souls: Remastered
This boss is optional. Reasons for fighting this boss include: (1) test your
mettle against a difficult mini-boss; (2) obtain some extra souls; (3) be
rewarded with Demon Titanite. As an SL1 character, you are unable to wield the
majority of weapons that can be upgraded with Demon Titanite. Of those items
that are upgraded with Demon Titanite, the only item you can properly wield
(both one- and two-handed) is the Crystal Ring Shield. If you still insist on
fighting this mini-boss, equip a 100% physical block shield and use the
Lightning Reinforced Club+4.
Darkroot Garden
46. Locations of Wolf Ring & Enchanted Ember, Dark Souls: Remastered
Let's visit Darkroot Garden to collect various items. First on the list is the
Wolf Ring. The ring grants you 40 Poise so you would not stagger when taking a
hit from various enemies. As an SL1 character, you cannot afford to tank hits,
meaning that the Wolf Ring is almost useless for the playthrough. The next item
to collect is the Enchanted Ember. Give the ember to Rickert and he would be
able to upgrade your weapons along the enchanted path. An enchanted weapon deals
magic damage, useful against bosses such as Ceaseless Discharge, Centipede
Demon, and Ornstein (both phases). Useful items to collect along the way:

Large Soul of a Nameless Soldier x 2
Soul of a Proud Knight
Large Soul of a Brave Warrior
Soul of a Brave Warrior

The next boss is optional. The main reason for defeating the Moonlight Butterfly
is to collect the Divine Ember which, together with the Dark Ember, is required
for upgrading a weapon along the Occult path. You should already have the Occult
Club when you collected Havel's armour set at Anor Londo. In case you want an
Occult Reinforced Club, then fighting the Moonlight Butterfly is mandatory.
Moonlight Butterfly (optional)
47. SL1 Moonlight Butterfly & Divine Ember, Dark Souls: Remastered
Fighting this boss is all about waiting for an opportunity to attack. The boss
constantly hovers above you and occasionally perches on the bridge to give you a
window to attack. Use some kind of ranged attacks while the boss is hovering,
e.g. Throwing Knife, (Black) Firebomb, Light Crossbow and bolts. When the boss
perches on the bridge, two-hand the Lightning Reinforced Club+4 and R2 it to
death.
Anor Londo
48. SL1 Cheese the Prowling Demon at Anor Londo, Dark Souls: Remastered
In case you need to collect Demon Titanite for some purpose, defeat the Prowling
Demon at Anor Londo. This mini-boss is easy to cheese. Have at least 80 Black
Firebombs; about 71 are enough. Purchase Black Firebombs from the Crestfallen
Merchant at Sen's Fortress. Start from the bonfire where you saw Solaire
sitting. Run up the circular staircase, turn left into a room, and go to the
balcony above the Prowling Demon. Throw Black Firebombs at the demon until it is
defeated.
Demon Ruins
49. How to get Sunlight Maggot, Dark Souls: Remastered
50. How to get Sunlight Maggot by using Poison Mist, Dark Souls: Remastered
Start from the Daughter of Chaos bonfire. Donate Humanity x 30 to Queelag's
sister to allow you to open the shortcut at Demon Ruins. Run to the bonfire
where a Burrowing Rockworm originally spawned. From there continue down the
flight of stairs and be in front of the fog wall to the arena of the Demon
Firesage. Do not enter the boss room. Instead, turn right and gingerly traverse
the path along the tree root and you should see a gigantic gate, in front of
which are various Chaos Bugs. Interact with the gate and it would open a
shortcut to Lost Izalith. Find a red-eyed Chaos Bug and kill it. The bug should
drop the Sunlight Maggot. You can also kill the bug from behind the gate. Attune
Poison Mist and Toxic Mist. Run to the gate, then cast Poison Mist followed by
Toxic Mist. The mist should reach the red-eyed Chaos Bug. Wait for the bug to
die. Either open the shortcut now (provided you have already donated Humanity x
30 to Queelag's sister) or wait until after you have defeated the Centipede
Demon. In any case, Solaire would not be able to collect the Sunlight Maggot,
thus you would have saved him from going insane.

doc/chaos-flame-ember.html.title: Chaos Flame Ember
doc/chaos-flame-ember.html.body:
Chaos Flame Ember
The Chaos Flame Ember allows you to upgrade a weapon along the Chaos path. Like
a Fire weapon, a Chaos weapon deals fire damage. So why would you not stick to a
Fire weapon? The reason is that the damage output of a Chaos weapon scales with
the number of soft Humanities you have, whereas a Fire weapon does not scale
with your soft Humanities nor your stats. You are SL1, remember? As a quick
comparison, suppose you have a Fire Reinforced Club+10 (the maximum possible
upgrade level for a Fire weapon) and a Chaos Reinforced Club+4 (the maximum
possible upgrade level is +5). It does not matter whether you one- or two-hand
your weapon.

The Fire Reinforced Club+10 has 232 Physical damage and 232 Fire damage, a
total of 465 AR.
At 0 soft Humanities, the Chaos Reinforced Club+4 has 187 Physical damage
and 213 Fire damage, a total of 400 AR.
At 10 soft Humanities, the Chaos Reinforced Club+4 has 227 Physical damage
and 257 Fire damage, a total of 484 AR.

A Chaos weapon deals more fire damage than a Fire weapon. Farming Humanity
consumables is not difficult. Equip the Covetous Gold Serpent Ring you grabbed
at Sen's Fortress and farm the rats at the Depths. For better drop rates, have a
few soft Humanities, preferably 10. You have access to another Humanity farm at
the Duke's Archives and in the area before the arena of Gravelord Nito. The best
Humanity farm is the Chasm of the Abyss in the DLC.
Lower Blighttown
If you have not done so, return to Firelink Shrine and exhaust Siegmeyer's
dialogue. Then go to lower Blighttown, where you should find him standing near a
gang of Giant Leeches. Exhaust his dialogue there and gift him some Purple Moss
Clumps to advance his quest line. The next time you meet him would be in Lost
Izalith.
Demon Firesage
51. SL1 Demon Firesage, Dark Souls: Remastered
Similar to the Stray Demon, except for its magic attack and tendency to jump
backward. Equip the Lightning Reinforced Club+4. Use R2 to quickly close the
distance. The boss can bleed, but it usually requires a couple of hits. With
quick enough attacks, you can bleed the boss at least 2 times during the fight.
Stay close in front of the boss to restrict its move set. When the boss jumps
backward, dash along with the boss and look out for an overhead attack or a
magic attack. When the boss hovers upward, move away to avoid the subsequent
butt slam and run in for a hit.
Defeat the Demon Firesage, dash down the flight of stairs, and light the
bonfire. Be ready for the next boss fight.
Centipede Demon
52. SL1 Centipede Demon, Dark Souls: Remastered
Equip the Lightning Reinforced Club+4. Equip the Gold-Hemmed set and the Flame
Stoneplate Ring to boost your fire defense. Enter the fog wall and head right
until you see a shiny. You want to be on that area because it provides plenty of
room for combat. Wait for the boss to approach you. At a distance, the boss
tends to perform a thrust attack with one of its arms. Roll sideway away from
the attack. Refrain from attacking the boss' arms. Cutting off an arm (or the
boss' tail) and you would have to deal with a still moving appendage in addition
to the boss itself. In general, you should hit the boss' head and/or its legs.
Being up close to the boss and it would most likely jump up in the air in an
attempt to hit you with a slam attack. Run as far away from the boss as possible
and for extra precaution roll away. The boss has a quick upward jump where it
would shoot a fireball at the ground. Use the same tactic by running or rolling
away. Sometimes the boss would attempt to grab you with its smaller and shorter
arm. Roll away from this attack and you should be safe from having the boss
chewing your character.
Lost Izalith
Defeat the Centipede Demon and be rewarded with the Orange Charred Ring. Equip
the ring to allow you to sprint through the various lava pools. You would still
receive damage, but the HP damage is massively reduced as compared to when you
do not have the ring equipped. Collect the Green Titanite Shard x 2, then dash
to the next bonfire en route to Lost Izalith. You should see Solaire sitting
despondently near the bonfire. Exhaust his dialogue to advance his quest line.
53. Lost Izalith: Red Titanite Chunk x 6 & Red Titanite Slab, Dark Souls: Remastered
Wade through the lava swamp filled with Bounding Demons of Izalith, creatures
that resemble the end half of a T-rex. Find a hidden bonfire and from there
navigate to Lost Izalith proper, where you can advance Siegmeyer's quest line.
Find him snoring above Chaos Eater x 4. Do not talk to him yet. Rather you
should use a crossbow and bolts to dispatch of Chaos Eater x 3. As for the
fourth Chaos Eater, shoot enough bolts at it to decrease its HP enough so that
Siegmeyer would be able to one-shot the enemy. Now equip the Rusted Iron Ring,
exhaust Siegmeyer's dialogue, and he would then drop down into the swamp and
charge at the remaining lone Chaos Eater. Attack the enemy if you want, but be
careful not to hit Siegmeyer as well. A fifth Chaos Eater can be found hiding in
a corner, trying to ambush you. Quickly defeat this enemy before it has a chance
to kill Siegmeyer. Get rid of all Chaos Eaters in the poison swamp and exhaust
Siegmeyer's dialogue. The Chaos Eaters drop Red Titanite Chunk (base 10% drop
rate), Red Titanite Slab (base 0.3%), and White Titanite Chunk (base 0.2%). The
Chaos Eater x 5 in the swamp do not respawn. If you are lucky they would drop a
few Red Titanite Chunks to help upgrade your Chaos weapon to +4. Run to the
corridor where you collected the Sunlight Maggot and you should see Solaire
sitting, again despondently. Exhaust his dialogue to advance his quest line.
Useful items to collect along the way:

Large Soul of a Brave Warrior
Soul of a Hero
Soul of a Brave Warrior x 2
Rare Ring of Sacrifice. This item is useful during your first encounter with
Seath the Scaleless.
Red Titanite Chunk x 2. One is found in the swamp near the Chaos Eater x 5.
The second is found near the root you used to descend into the swamp, and
near a Chaos Eater.
Green Titanite Shard x 2. Near the Chaos Eater x 5 in the poison swamp.
Red Titanite Slab. In a wooden chest in the swamp.

Bed of Chaos
54. SL1 Bed of Chaos, "best" boss in the game, Dark Souls: Remastered
A mandatory gimmick fight where you must destroy two tree roots on either side
of the arena in order to unlock the real boss. The whole fight itself is
tedious, but at least you can quit and save your progress after destroying each
tree root. Bring along the Longbow and plenty of arrows. Enter the fog wall,
slide down the inclined plane, and dash to your right to destroy the root at the
right end of the arena. Find a corner close to the root and shoot arrows at the
root. You need to first break various branches protecting the root, then shoot
arrows at the root. When you see a cutscene plays, skip the cutscene and quit to
the main menu and load your game again. You would be placed in front of the fog
wall again, but your progress with the fight is also saved. Enter the fog wall
the second time, slide down, and dash to your left. Find a corner to snipe the
root at the left end of the arena. When you see another cutscene plays, quit and
reload as per above. Enter the fog wall the third time. Your target this time is
the boss straight ahead. Gingerly push forward and drop down onto a root, being
careful not to be pushed over the edge by the giant arms. Walk or run upward
along the root, rolling to break the various branches that block your way.
Eventually you should see a bug; that is the true boss of the fight. Use a
Reinforced Club to hit the boss and the fight should be over.
A quick cheese method consists of using the
Tokhi bombs strategy. Refer
to the video below for an explanation.
How To CHEESE Bed Of Chaos [Firebomb Strat] | Dark Souls Guides
After both roots are destroyed, the only thing left to do is roll through the
various branches ahead and find the Chaos Bug. The tunnel to the Chaos Bug is
dangerous. As your character rolls through the tunnel, the boss can perform the
Volcanic Chaos attack where pillars of flames erupt. The tunnel does not afford
much room to manoeuvre and your character would most likely be killed by the
flame. You must then journey to the fog wall again and fight the second phase of
the boss, aka the most annoying phase.
55. Demon Ruins: Chaos Flame Ember & other treasures, Dark Souls: Remastered
Defeat the Bed of Chaos. Navigate to the area that was previously completely
flooded with lava before you defeated Ceaseless Discharge. Equip the Orange
Charred Ring and find a shiny in a lava pool. That is the Chaos Flame Ember.

doc/very-large-ember.html.title: Very Large Ember
doc/very-large-ember.html.body:
Very Large Ember
The Very Large Ember allows Andre to ascend various weapons from +10 to +11. For
example, give the Very Large Ember to Andre and he would be able to ascend your
Reinforced Club+10 to a Reinforced Club+11. You require a few Titanite Chunks to
upgrade the weapon to +14 and a Titanite Slab to attain the maximum level of
+15.
Upper Blighttown
56. Location of Power Within, Dark Souls: Remastered
Generally, this area is not worth exploring save for collecting the pyromancy
Power Within. A rule for the current SL1 run is to not use any pyromancy against
bosses. This includes Power Within as well. In case you plan on using Power
Within in subsequent SL1 runs, e.g. an SL1 run in NG+1 and beyond, now is a good
time to grab the pyromancy. Start from the Depths bonfire and use the Blighttown
Key to access upper Blighttown. Head on down to the Parasitic Wall Hugger, kill
the creature, and grab the shiny underneath.
Anor Londo
57. Anor Londo: Titanite Chunk, Dark Souls: Remastered
Before you have access to unflooded New Londo Ruins, the Royal Sentinel x 2
found in front of the arena of Ornstein and Smough are your best source of
Titanite Chunks. You should have farmed these enemies prior to defeating
Ornstein and Smough by summoning Solaire to help you farm. It is a nightmare
fighting the Royal Sentinel x 2 and the nearby Silver Knight by yourself.
But do not despair. A Titanite Chunk is available to be collected. From the
Chamber of the Princess bonfire, find the Giant Blacksmith. From his location,
you should see a balcony at the edge of which is a shiny. That is a Titanite
Chunk.
Darkroot Garden
Sooner or later you would need access to New Londo Ruins to fight the Four
Kings. You require two items to unlock the boss fight:

Lordvessel. You should already have this item after defeating Ornstein and
Smough, and exhausting the dialogue of Gwynevere.
Covenant of Artorias. This ring is dropped by Sif, a boss at Darkroot
Garden.

Let's grab the second item.
Great Grey Wolf Sif
58. SL1 Great Grey Wolf Sif, Dark Souls: Remastered
Sif is weak against fire. Two-hand your Fire Reinforced Club+10. If you have a
Chaos Reinforced Club+4, use that instead and have at least 10 soft Humanities.
Enter the arena and interact with the massive sword in front of a gravestone to
initiate the fight. Position your character underneath the boss to avoid its
horizontal swipes. R1 or R2 a hind leg. Sif tends to jump away from you. Expect
much of the fight to be chasing it.
Defeat Sif and be rewarded with the Covenant of Artorias.
New Londo Ruins
59. New Londo Ruins flooded: Key to the Seal, Transient Curse x 6, Rare Ring of Sacrifice
Start from Firelink Shrine and visit the Undead Female Merchant to purchase all
Transient Curses from her. Head down to New Londo Ruins. Your objective is to
rendezvous with Ingward, who would gift you the Key to the Seal. You require
this item to open the flood gates of New Londo Ruins and unlock the lower
portion of the area. Use a Transient Curse to allow you to fight the ghosts
scattered throughout New Londo Ruins. The ghosts drop Transient Curse. Farm the
ghosts if you need more Transient Curses, but farming is not necessary because
you can purchase the item from Ingward. On your way to Ingward, you should be
able to collect Transient Curse x 6 and a Rare Ring of Sacrifice. Ingward stands
on the roof of a building. Reach him by climbing an iron ladder and exhaust his
dialogue to receive the Key to the Seal. Use the key to unlock the gate to a
lever and turn the lever to release the flood gates, hence unlocking the lower
portion of New Londo Ruins. Here are some useful items to collect along the way:

Large Soul of a Nameless Soldier x 2
Soul of a Proud Knight
Cursebite Ring
Green Titanite Shard
Humanity

60. New Londo Ruins unflooded: Very Large Ember & Titanite Chunk x 2, Dark Souls: Remastered
The unflooded lower portion of New Londo Ruins has Titanite Chunk x 2 and the
Very Large Ember. The area provides the best source of Titanite Chunks, i.e. the
Darkwraiths. Other useful items to collect include:

Large Soul of a Proud Knight x 3
Humanity
Soul of a Brave Warrior

Grab the Very Large Ember and hand it over to Andre. You should have enough
Titanite Chunks to upgrade the Reinforced Club to at least +12. Farm the
Darkwraiths for Titanite Chunks to upgrade the weapon to +14. If you are lucky a
Darkwraith might drop a Titanite Slab to allow you to upgrade the weapon to +15.
Four Kings
61. SL1 Four Kings, Dark Souls: Remastered
This gank boss is weak against lightning. Equip the Lightning Reinforced Club+5.
Equip the Covenant of Artorias so your character would not fall through the
arena and die. Stay close to a king, roll through a horizontal swipe (or a
thrust or overhead attack) to position your character behind the enemy, and get
in an R1. This fight has a time limit. The longer you drag out the fight, the
more enemies would spawn. Kill one enemy at a time and as fast as you can. As an
enemy performs its death animation, hit the dying enemy a few times to lower the
shared HP bar of the boss. When you see a purplish-blue aura around an enemy,
run or roll away because the enemy is charging up its AOE. When you see an enemy
raise up an arm to charge a purplish-blue disk, raise up your Grass Crest Shield
to block an incoming magic projectile.

doc/dark-ember.html.title: Dark Ember
doc/dark-ember.html.body:
Dark Ember
The Dark Ember allows Andre to ascend a +5 divine weapon along the occult path.
Occult weapons deal bonus damage against Gwyndolin and Gwyn. You should already
have the Occult Club, collected from a chest at Anor Londo. Stick to that occult
weapon. However, should you want to experiment with other occult weapons, then
collect the Dark Ember from the Painted World of Ariamis. Use White Titanite
Chunks to upgrade an occult weapon to +4. For now, farm White Titanite Chunks
from the Pinwheel Servants. There is a better farming location, available after
you have defeated Bed of Chaos, Four Kings, Gravelord Nito, and Seath the
Scaleless. You will pick up a White Titanite Slab in the DLC and use the slab to
fully upgrade an occult weapon.
Anor Londo
Start from the Darkmoon Tomb bonfire. Crank the lever of the spiral staircase so
the mechanism goes as low as it could. Descend the staircase to reach an area
filled with Painting Guardians. Defeat each enemy one at a time to allow you
safe passage to the massive painting at the back of the room. Interact with the
painting to be transported to a secret area.
Painted World of Ariamis
77. Painted World of Ariamis: cheese the Undead Dragon, Dark Souls: Remastered
78. Painted World of Ariamis: Large Titanite Shard, Dark Souls: Remastered
81. Location of Annex Key, Dark Souls: Remastered
82. Location of Dark Ember, Dark Souls: Remastered
Your objective is to collect the Annex Key to open a path leading to the Dark
Ember. Collect other treasures in the area if you want such as Dragon Scale,
Large Titanite Shard, and soul items. Get the Annex Key and collect the Dark
Ember, then fight the area boss to unlock the passage out of the painting.
Crossbreed Priscilla (optional)
79. SL1 Crossbreed Priscilla, Dark Souls: Remastered
This boss is difficult due to her invisibility. Two-hand a Lightning Reinforced
Club+5, enter the fog wall, and R2 her tail. Wait for Priscilla to become
invisible. Bait her into walking along the snow-covered floor, thus leaving a
trail of footsteps to allow you to figure out her position. Dash to her side or
behind her (I know she is invisible but you can figure out whether you are in
front or behind by looking at the position of her footsteps), get in an R1, and
roll away. Deal enough damage to Priscilla and she would become visible again.
Use the same strategy as before. Get behind Priscilla to allow you to safely
attack her.
80. Fire Keeper Soul from Darkmoon Knightess, Dark Souls: Remastered
Defeat Priscilla and approach the cliff edge to initiate a cutscene. You will
then be transported back to Anor Londo, in front of the massive painting. For an
extra Fire Keeper Soul, you might want to defeat the Darkmoon Knightess at the
Anor Londo bonfire. Find Andre and give him the Dark Ember.

doc/finish-dlc.html.title: Finish the DLC
doc/finish-dlc.html.body:
Finish the DLC
You can now go fight Gwyn if you want to end your SL1 playthrough. For the sake
of completeness, you might want to defeat the remaining two bosses of the DLC.
Oolacile Township
After defeating Artorias, light the Oolacile Township bonfire and do not consume
the Soul of Artorias.
88. SL1 Lord's Blade Ciaran, Dark Souls: Remastered
Lord's Blade Ciaran (optional)
An optional fight. The only reason to fight her is to obtain her armour set.
Ciaran also drops her weapons upon defeat, but you would not be able to properly
wield the weapons.
89. Oolacile Township: locations of Crest Key & Silver Pendant, Dark Souls: Remastered
Defeat Ciaran. Then explore the rest of the area to collect the Crest Key and
the Silver Pendant, both of which are related to the two remaining bosses of the
DLC. The Crest Key opens the door to the tower where Hawkeye Gough sits. Gough
will help you to initiate the fight against Black Dragon Kalameet. The key is
found within a Mimic. The Silver Pendant is a magic weapon that can deflect the
sorcery of Manus. The pendant is found inside a chest behind an illusory wall.
As you approach the wall, you will hear a pounding noise. Equip the Sunlight
Maggot and you should see an opening. Be vigilant while exploring the general
area because the enemies can one- or two-shot you. Another reason to be vigilant
is that Marvelous Chester will invade you. Other useful items to collect in the
area include:

Large Soul of a Proud Knight
Soul of a Brave Warrior x 2
Red Titanite Chunk. Found inside a chest, hidden behind an illusory wall. As
you approach the wall, you will hear a pounding noise. Equip the Sunlight
Maggot near the source of the noise and an opening would reveal itself.
Twin Humanities
Soul of a Hero

Chasm of the Abyss
90. Chasm of the Abyss: White Titanite Slab, Dark Souls: Remastered
This is the best area in the game for farming Humanities. The Humanity Phantoms
have the highest Humanity drop rates in the game. The only item worth collecting
is the White Titanite Slab near the fog wall to the arena of Manus. You need
this slab to fully upgrade the Occult Reinforced Club to +5. Other useful items
to collect in the area include:

Humanity
Twin Humanities
Soul of a Hero

Manus, Father of the Abyss (optional)
92. SL1 Manus, Father of the Abyss, Dark Souls: Remastered
One of the more difficult bosses in the DLC. Equip the Lightning Reinforced
Club+5 (or the Blacksmith Giant Hammer+5 if you have it) and trigger the effect
of the Red Tearstone Ring. Equip the Mask of the Child and the Grass Crest
Shield. Phase one is the easier phase. Avoid or roll through Manus' hand slam
and hand swipe attacks. Bait a jumping hand slam attack, or a delayed hand slam,
then R2. Phase two is the more dangerous phase of the fight. Manus will perform
three magic attacks. The first magic attack is when he charges his staff and
strikes it into the sky, after which a barrage of magic orbs showers upon you.
Sprint away from Manus and the orbs. The second magic attack is where Manus
charges his staff and impales it into the ground. A barrage of magic orbs wells
up from the ground and encircles you. Sprint to Manus and R2 and the orbs would
not hit you. The third magic attack occurs when Manus charges his staff and
shoots a volley of orbs directly at you. Dash or roll to the side. You can use
the Silver Pendant to deflect all of the above magic orbs. Like in phase one,
bait the hand slam and R2.
Defeat Manus and exhaust Dusk's dialogue. Revisit Elizabeth near the Oolacile
Sanctuary bonfire. Exhaust her dialogue and she would reward you with
Elizabeth's Mushroom x 3.
Go to the cliff above the arena of Kalameet. The dragon would fly above you.
Wait for the dragon to fly out of sight, then use the Crest Key to visit Gough.
Exhaust his dialogue and answer "Yes" to his questions. A cutscene would play
wherein Gough shoots down Kalameet, meaning that you can now fight the dragon.
Black Dragon Kalameet (optional)
93. SL1 Black Dragon Kalameet, Dark Souls: Remastered
This boss is a colossal tank. Equip the Lightning Reinforced Club+5 or the
Blacksmith Giant Hammer+5 if you have it. Equip the Grass Crest Shield and the
Mask of the Child. Trigger the effect of the Red Tearstone Ring as follows. Use
the Symbol of Avarice to decrease your HP to about 622. Enter the fog wall and
drop down to the ledge where a Crystal Lizard can be found. Drop down again to
the floor of the arena and the effect of the Red Tearstone Ring would trigger.
Enter the arena and wait for Kalameet to walk into the fight. Bait the flying
thrust attack, dash underneath the tail, wait for Kalameet to slam its tail, and
R2. Rinse and repeat until the tail is cut. Another strategy is to be up close
to the dragon. Be by its side, bait the stomping attack, roll or move out of the
range of the attack, then R2. This strategy might sound dangerous, but it is
safer than trying to bait the flying thrust attack. Beware that Kalameet can
hover upward to breathe fire down on you. In that case, sprint away and wait for
the fire to dissipate. The boss might also perform a delayed charged attack to
position itself away from you so it can perform some of its fire and/or swipe
attacks.
94. Royal Wood after Kalameet: Twinkling Titanite x 2 & Titanite Slab, Dark Souls: Remastered
Defeat Kalameet then collect the treasures within the arena. A chest can be
found behind a waterfall. The chest contains a Titanite Slab. Reload the area to
respawn the Crystal Lizard, which drops Twinkling Titanite x 2. Other useful
items to collect include:

Soul of a Brave Warrior x 2
Soul of a Hero

doc/large-divine-ember.html.title: Large Divine Ember
doc/large-divine-ember.html.body:
Large Divine Ember
The Large Divine Ember allows Andre to ascend a divine weapon from +5 to +6. You
will need White Titanite Chunks and a White Titanite Slab to fully upgrade the
divine weapon to +10. A divine weapon allows you to kill any Skeletons without
having to first defeat their respective Necromancers. This feature of a divine
weapon is especially useful during the fight against Nito. You will face Nito in
addition to a gang of Skeletons that remain alive as long as Nito is alive.
However, you can use a divine weapon to kill the Skeletons and Nito would not be
able to revive them. You could downgrade the Occult Club you picked up at Anor
Londo into a Divine Club. For maximum flexibility, you might want to collect the
Divine Ember and Large Divine Ember so as to upgrade/ascend any divine weapon
you are able to properly wield.
The Great Hollow
75. Location of Cloranthy Ring, Dark Souls: Remastered
Although not strictly required, consider grabbing the Cloranthy Ring. The item
boosts your Stamina regeneration at a rate of 20 Stamina points per second.
Stack the ring with the Grass Crest Shield to boost your Stamina regeneration at
a rate of 30 Stamina points per second. Additionally equipping the Mask of the
Child would grant you an extra 10 Stamina points per second. You can equip the
above three items and also consume a Green Blossom for a total boost of 80
Stamina points per second.
Tomb of the Giants
70. Location of Large Divine Ember, Dark Souls: Remastered
You should have the Lordvessel before entering this area. It is easier to warp
into and out of this area than it is to navigate without the warping ability of
the Lordvessel. Furthermore, you should have collected the Sunlight Maggot.
Equip the head piece to allow you maximum visibility while navigating the area.
Rest at the Tomb of the Giants bonfire. Climb up the ladder and exhaust Patches'
dialogue. Answer "No" to his question and walk towards the nearby ledge to
initiate his quest line. You need to complete his quest line for him to be your
merchant. Patches will kick you off the ledge and down the pit below. Get out of
the pit or Homeward Bone to the Tomb of the Giants bonfire. Exhaust Patches'
dialogue again and answer "No" to his question. After defeating Nito, Patches
would relocate to Firelink Shrine, where you can purchase the Mask of the Child
from him.
Ascend a path to find a rectangular hole. Use a ladder to descend the hole. You
will find a gang of Giant Skeletons, each wielding the Murakumo. Each enemy is
tough, but to find them clumped together within a small area is the stuff of
nightmare. You can cheese the Giant Skeletons by standing near the ladder and
throw (Black) Firebombs at the enemies. Use bow/arrows and/or crossbow/bolts if
you want, but note that the Giant Skeletons can block with their weapons.
Pyromancy is another option. Skeletons are generally weak against fire. Cheese
the enemies and/or make a suicide run to collect the shiny at one end of the
area. That is the Large Divine Ember. Give the ember to Andre as soon as
possible.
Northern Undead Asylum
71. Trade with Snuggly for White Titanite Chunk, Dark Souls: Remastered
Rest at the Firelink Shrine bonfire. Your objective now is to trade a Sunlight
Medal with Snuggly to receive a White Titanite Chunk in return. You require
White Titanite Chunk x 7 to upgrade a divine weapon to +9. One White Titanite
Chunk can be obtained by trading with Snuggly. Use the giant crow to travel back
to the Northern Undead Asylum and locate Snuggly's nest. Stand on the nest, drop
a Sunlight Medal, quit to menu, reload the game, and you should be able to pick
up a White Titanite Chunk. Homeward Bone to the Firelink Shrine bonfire.
Tomb of the Giants
72. Location of Covetous Silver Serpent Ring, Dark Souls: Remastered
73. How to get Sanctus, Dark Souls: Remastered
Start from the Tomb of the Giants bonfire and equip the Sunlight Maggot to
provide you maximum visibility. If you plan on farming souls for whatever
purpose, you might want to grab the Covetous Silver Serpent Ring found in the
area. The path to the ring is also a shortcut to help you quickly navigate to
the path where Leeroy invades you. Take the shortcut, grab the ring, and go to
the location where Leeroy invades you. Two-hand the Fire Reinforced Club+10 and
R2 Leeroy. R2 x 2 should be enough to kill Leeroy. Do not give him any
opportunity to miracle heal. Kill Leeroy while he is standing on solid ground so
you can loot the Sanctus off him. Kicking Leeroy off the edge would also kill
him, but you would not be able to collect the Sanctus. While equipped, the
Sanctus regenerates your HP at a rate of 2 HP every 2 seconds.
74. Tomb of the Giants: White Titanite Chunk x 2 & White Titanite Slab, Dark Souls: Remastered
Enter the nearby cave to find a Crystal Lizard. You might need to quit to menu
and reload the game again in order to respawn the lizard. The lizard is
guaranteed to drop Twinkling Titanite x 2. If you are lucky it might also drop a
White Titanite Chunk. Push ahead to the area in front of the fog wall to Nito's
arena. You will encounter a number of Pinwheel Servants as well as Baby
Skeletons. Defeat the Pinwheel Servants; the Baby Skeletons can be left alone.
The area has White Titanite Chunk x 2 and a White Titanite Slab. You will need
the slab to upgrade the Divine Reinforced Club to +10, which will be useful
during the fight against Nito. Here are other useful items to collect:

Soul of a Hero x 2
Mask of the Child. Can be farmed from the Pinwheel Servants in front of
Nito's arena.
White Titanite Chunk. Also farmed from the Pinwheel Servants before the fog
wall of Nito's arena. Farm the Pinwheel Servants until you have enough White
Titanite Chunks to upgrade the Divine Reinforced Club to +9. Then use the
White Titanite Slab to upgrade the weapon to +10.

Gravelord Nito
76. SL1 Gravelord Nito, Dark Souls: Remastered
This boss is rather easy by himself. The fight is difficult due to his Skeleton
minions, who can gank you to death. Nito is the Skeletons' necromancer, meaning
that you should use the Divine Reinforced Club+10 to get rid of the Skeletons
prior to dealing with Nito. Equip the Fire Reinforced Club+10, the Divine
Reinforced Club+10, and the Cloranthy Ring. Nito's attacks can build up your
toxic metre. Be sure to stock up on Blooming Purple Moss Clumps before entering
the fight. Enter the fog wall and drop down into the arena. Nito would most
likely begin with a sword stab that can reach you from almost anywhere within
the arena. Stay where you are, avoid the attack if possible, and wait for a gang
of Skeletons to approach you. Use the Crest Shield to block a Skeleton's attack
and use the Divine Reinforced Club+10 to kill the Skeleton. Rinse and repeat for
the remaining Skeletons. Do not approach Nito; let him come to you. Furthermore,
do not be near the general area where you first saw Nito because that area is
filled with Giant Skeleton x 2 who are waiting to ambush you. Stay near the area
where you dropped down. Wait for Nito to approach you and use the Fire
Reinforced Club+10 to fight him. His melee attacks are slow and easy to dodge.
Nito would occasionally charge up an AOE attack. Sprint as far away from him as
possible to be outside the range of the attack. Alternatively, use the Crest
Shield to block the AOE attack.
Defeat Nito and return to Firelink Shrine. Find Patches squatting near the area
where Frampt spawned. Patches is now your merchant. The most useful item he
sells is the Mask of the Child because the item boosts your Stamina regeneration
at a rate of 10 Stamina points per second. The effect stacks with the Grass
Crest Shield and the Cloranthy Ring.

doc/reinforced-club+6.html.title: Reinforced Club+6
doc/reinforced-club+6.html.body:
Reinforced Club+6
In which you upgrade your main weapon to +6.
Lower Undead Burg
14. Lower Undead Burg: treasures & Blooming Purple Moss Clump, Dark Souls: Remastered
A shortcut connects Firelink Shrine and a route to the Capra Demon. For now, aim
to open this shortcut and grab the following treasures:

Twin Humanities
Large Soul of a Lost Undead x 2
Blooming Purple Moss Clump. Sold by the Undead Female Merchant. The moss
will be useful to remove the toxic status effect inflicted by the Blowdart
Snipers in Blighttown. The merchant also sells Purple Moss Clump (another
useful consumable when you visit Blighttown) and Transient Curse (useful
when you visit New Londo Ruins). Purchase at least 2 or 3 Blooming Purple
Moss Clumps.

Northern Undead Asylum
5. North. Undead Asylum: Twinkling Titanitex4, Titanite Chunk, Red Titanite Chunkx2, Peculiar Doll
16. Location of Rusted Iron Ring, Dark Souls: Remastered
Revisit the Northern Undead Asylum to collect various items that will be useful
later in the game. Use the elevator at Firelink Shrine to access a platform that
allows you to roll off onto a buttress. Ascend the buttress and a spiral
staircase to reach a crow nest. Curl up in the nest and the giant crow would
take you back to the Northern Undead Asylum. Here is a list of useful items to
collect:

Rusted Iron Ring. The ring allows you to walk and sprint unencumbered in
various bodies of water as well as the swamp of Lower Blighttown.
Twinkling Titanite x 4. Obtained by trading Blood Red Moss Clump, Purple
Moss Clump, and Blooming Purple Moss Clump with Snuggly.
Titanite Chunk. Obtained by trading Rubbish with Snuggly.
Red Titanite Chunk x 2. Guaranteed drop by Black Knight x 2.
Peculiar Doll. Found in the cell where you originally spawned at the start
of the game.

Lower Undead Burg
Defeat the Capra Demon to obtain the Key to the Depths. You require this key to
access the Depths, where you can collect the Large Ember to ascend your weapons
to +6.
Capra Demon
17. SL1 Capra Demon, Dark Souls: Remastered
The real boss of this fight are the Attack Dog x 2. Prioritize defeating these
enemies as quickly as possible. Equip the Heater Shield in the left hand and the
Reinforced Club+5 in the right hand. Upon entering the fog wall, block with the
shield and sprint to the staircase. Ascend the stairs, then turn right and
position your character at the top-right corner of the arena. Use the shield to
block the attacks of the Capra Demon and wait for it to drop off the edge. Wait
for the Attack Dogs to approach you and kill them one at a time. A one-handed R1
would likely result in your weapon bouncing off the wall. The fight against the
Capra Demon is much easier once the Attack Dogs are taken care of.
Defeat the Capra Demon and use the Key to the Depths to access the Depths.
The Depths
18. Location of Large Ember, Dark Souls: Remastered
The main purpose of going to the Depths is to collect the Large Ember. Some
bodies of water in the area can restrict your movement. Equip the Rusted Iron
Ring to help you explore the area unencumbered. The Large Ember is found inside
a chest, guarded by a Butcher and an Attack Dog. Deal with the nearby Hollows
first, then the Attack Dog, and finally fight the Butcher.
19. The Depths: rescue Laurentius, Dark Souls: Remastered
20. The Depths: Large Titanite Shard & Spider Shield, Dark Souls: Remastered
Rescue Laurentius, a pyromancer who sells various pyromancy spells that are
useful for an SL1 character. Exhaust his dialogue. The next time you meet him
would be at Firelink Shrine. A Large Titanite Shard can be found in the Depths
as well as the Spider Shield, which has better stability than the Heater Shield.
The other useful aspect of the Spider Shield is its ability to block 100% of
poison attacks from Infested Barbarians and 100% toxic attacks from Blowdart
Snipers. The shield is generally useful to help you explore Blighttown. The
Heavy Crossbow, also found in the Depths, can be wielded by an SL1 character,
but must be two-handed unlike the Light Crossbow. Other useful items include:

Soul of a Nameless Soldier x 5
Large Soul of a Nameless Soldier x 2
Sewer Chamber Key. Use this key to open the door that leads to the bonfire
at the Depths. The key is not required if you have the Master Key.
Humanity
Ring of the Evil Eye

Make your way to Andre at Undead Parish, give him the Large Ember, and use his
services to ascend the Reinforced Club+5 to +6. You should have bought the
Weapon Smith Box by now. The bonfire item allows you to upgrade your weapons.
However, you still require the services of Andre to ascend your weapons.
Gaping Dragon (optional)
21. SL1 Gaping Dragon, Dark Souls: Remastered
You should have gotten rid of the Channeler to preempt the enemy from sniping
magic at you while you fight the boss. This boss is not any more difficult than
during your normal playthrough. Two-hand the Reinforced Club+6. You do not need
to buff the weapon with Gold Pine Resin. Save it for more difficult bosses later
in the game. Enter the fog wall and start the fight by sprinting to the boss,
which should start off by slamming its snout onto the ground. Aim your R2 at the
snout and move away to the side because the boss would perform a walking
charging attack. Move along with the boss, wait for it to stop walking, and R2
its tail. Whenever the opportunity presents itself, try to R2 the tail to cut it
off. The boss fight is a little easier with the tail cut off. Stay in front of
the boss and close to it to bait the snout slam again so you can get in an R2 on
the snout. Rinse and repeat as per above. Be wary of the hand swipe, the tail
swipe, the jumping stomp, and the leg stomp. The boss also has a retch attack,
where it vomits and the goo would expand along the ground to cover a wide area.
Run as far away from the boss as possible to be outside the range of the vomit.
Defeat the boss and be rewarded with the Blighttown Key. You do not need this
key because the Master Key can open a shortcut to Lower Blighttown.

doc/titanite-slab.html.title: Titanite Slab from Sieglinde
doc/titanite-slab.html.body:
Titanite Slab from Sieglinde
Apart from the Stray Demon, another guaranteed Titanite Slab is obtained after
completing the quest lines of Siegmeyer and Sieglinde. You should have already
completed Siegmeyer's quest line by now. The last time you interacted with him
should have been at Lost Izalith, where he was snoring above a gang of Chaos
Eaters. Now let's follow Sieglinde's quest line. It is safe to ignore
Sieglinde's quest line altogether if you do not want any other Titanite Slabs.
Proceed with her quest line nonetheless in case you want to experiment with a
different upgraded weapon.
Darkroot Basin
First, rescue Dusk as doing so would fulfil a criterion for accessing the DLC.
Go to Darkroot Basin and clear the area of all Crystal Golems. You do not want
these enemies to harass you while you fight the Hydra. In fact, you can use the
water projectiles of the Hydra to kill the golems.
Hydra (optional)
62. SL1 Hydra at Darkroot Basin, rescue Dusk, Dark Souls: Remastered
Equip the Crest Shield+5 and the Lightning Heavy Crossbow+4 (with Sniper Bolts).
Do not grab the shiny in front of the Hydra. Use this shiny to help you figure
out a safe location to stand. Block with your shield and wait for the Hydra to
thrust its heads at you. Then two-hand the crossbow and shoot a bolt at the
boss. You can safely shoot at most 2 bolts before you must raise your shield
again. Rinse and repeat until the boss is defeated.
Defeat the Hydra and be rewarded with Dragon Scale and Dusk Crown Ring. The
shiny alluded to above is the Knight armour set. Now equip the Rusted Iron Ring
and head left along the coast until you find an alcove. If you do not see a
golden Crystal Golem, quit and reload your game to spawn the golem. Defeat the
golem and Dusk should spawn. Exhaust her dialogue and answer "Yes" to her
question. Run back to the location where you fought the Hydra to find Dusk's
summon sign. Summon Dusk, learn her gesture, and purchase anything you need from
her. Then exhaust her dialogue to advance her quest line.
The Duke's Archives
63. How to get Broken Pendant, Dark Souls: Remastered
64. The Duke's Archives: Twinkling Titanite x 4, Dark Souls: Remastered
Next, let's grab the Broken Pendant. This item is one of two prerequisites for
accessing the DLC. The first is rescuing Dusk. Go to the Duke's Archives and
ride the first elevator up. You should see a Crystal Golem facing a corner.
Defeat the golem to be rewarded with the Broken Pendant. The area has Twinkling
Titanite x 4. You can ignore them because they can be purchased from the Giant
Blacksmith. You might also want to collect a Soul of a Brave Warrior in the
area.
65. The Duke's Archives: Crystal Ember, Twinkling Titanite, Fire Keeper Soul, Dark Souls: Remastered
67. The Duke's Archives: Blue Titanite Chunk, Dark Souls: Remastered
Enter the first boss room of Seath the Scaleless. This is a mandatory death.
Equip the Rare Ring of Sacrifice prior to entering the arena. (There is a way to
skip the first encounter with Seath, but the skip will not be discussed here.)
Let Seath kill your character and revive within a jail cell. Kill the nearby
Serpent Soldier, grab the Archive Tower Cell Key, and use the key to break out
of your jail cell. The most useful item to collect in the area is the Fire
Keeper Soul, locked in a cell behind a bunch of Pisacas. The cell can be opened
with the Archive Tower Giant Cell Key. To get the key, you need the Archive
Tower Giant Door Key. If you have been following Logan's quest line, he should
be within the same cell as the Fire Keeper Soul. Rescue Logan if you want, but
doing so is not necessary to complete your SL1 playthrough. Other useful items
to collect in the area include:

Crystal Ember. Give this to the Giant Blacksmith and he would be able to
ascend weapons along the crystal path.
Blue Titanite Chunk x 2
Twinkling Titanite
Soul of a Brave Warrior
Large Soul of a Brave Warrior

66. Rescue Sieglinde, Dark Souls: Remastered
Your next objective should be to initiate the quest line of Sieglinde. Near
where you grabbed the Crystal Ember, pull a lever to reveal a flight of
descending stairs. Go down, through the fog wall, and find a golden Crystal
Golem. Do not trigger the fight with the golden golem yet. First, defeat the
nearby Crystal Golems in the area, then defeat the golden golem to rescue
Sieglinde. Exhaust Sieglinde's dialogue and answer "Yes" to her question. The
next time you meet her would be at Firelink Shrine; warp to Firelink Shrine and
exhaust her dialogue there. You should already have completed Siegmeyer's quest
line at Lost Izalith. Warp to Firelink Shrine again (or quit and reload your
game), exhaust Sieglinde's dialogue again, and answer "Yes" to her question. She
should now relocate to Ash Lake.
Seath the Scaleless
68. SL1 Seath the Scaleless, Dark Souls: Remastered
This boss is weak against fire and lightning. Use a Chaos Reinforced Club+4 or a
Lightning Reinforced Club+5. Equip the Red Tearstone Ring and decrease your HP
low enough to trigger its effect. The fight is a battle against time. The longer
you drag it out, the more dangerous Seath becomes due to the boss' dragon breath
and its curse build up. Enter the boss arena and stand near the glowing crystal.
Wait for Seath to approach you. When the boss is close enough, it would attempt
to perform an attack. Before the attack happens, roll into the crystal to break
it, thus stunning Seath for a brief moment. Take the opportunity to dash to the
boss and be up close. R1 or R2 the boss and always be very close to avoid any
attacks.
Defeat Seath. If you have been following Logan's quest line, he can now be found
sitting near The Duke's Archives bonfire. Find Logan, exhaust his dialogue, and
purchase all his sorceries to further his quest line. Then exhaust his dialogue
again.
Ash Lake
69. Complete Sieglinde's quest line & Titanite Slab, Dark Souls: Remastered
You will now complete Sieglinde's quest line. Head on down to lower Blighttown.
Equip the Rusted Iron Ring to allow you unfettered movement within the swamp.
Locate and ascend a giant tree root. Break through two illusory walls and enter
The Great Hollow. Descend the various giant roots and navigate to Ash Lake.
Sieglinde is found standing near the very first bonfire at Ash Lake. Exhaust her
dialogue and be rewarded with a Titanite Slab.

doc/lordvessel.html.title: Lordvessel
doc/lordvessel.html.body:
Lordvessel
The Lordvessel allows you to teleport between most bonfires, saving you a lot of
time sprinting between bonfires. The item is also used to unlock various endgame
areas, including the final boss of the game.
Sen's Fortress
36. Sen's Fortress: Titanite Chunk from first giant, Dark Souls: Remastered
Sen's Fortress, aka the Funhouse, has materials for upgrading the Reinforced
Club as well as other useful items. First, let's grab a Titanite Chunk from the
giant who opened the gate to Sen's Fortress. Start from the Undead Parish
bonfire and dash into the Funhouse and past the Serpent Soldier x 2. Run up the
small flight of stairs, turn left, and drop down onto the platform near an
entrance to a ladder. Ensure you have a full HP bar before dropping off the
ledge. After dropping down, roll into the entrance and turn right to avoid a
possible lightning attack from the nearby Prowling Demon. Heal up as necessary.
Climb up the ladder and grab a Large Soul of a Proud Knight. Wait a while to see
whether a Serpent Soldier follow you up the ladder. Attack an illusory wall to
reveal another ladder. Climb the second ladder to meet up with the giant who
opened the gate. The giant can be tricky to fight. Equip the Fire Reinforced
Club+7, stay behind the giant, get out of the range of his stomps and tantrum
attacks, and get in one or more R2. Defeat the giant to collect a Titanite
Chunk. Homeward Bone to the Undead Parish bonfire.
37. Sen's Fortress: Large Titanite Shard x 2 & Covetous Gold Serpent Ring, Dark Souls: Remastered
Start from the Undead Parish bonfire again. Enter the gate of the fortress and
defeat the Serpent Soldier x 2. Each Serpent Soldier can be parried and
riposted. Make your way along the tricky narrow platform guarded by a Serpent
Soldier, get past the enemy, and meet up with the Serpent Mage who guards
another narrow platform. Use the pressure plate to activate a trap to kill the
enemy and grab Large Titanite Shard x 2 from a wooden chest. Rescue Big Hat
